## 6. Milestones

### MVP (v1.0) — single coding pass

A working three-pane app that persists a virtual library of `.md` and `.txt` files and lets you edit them as plain text with Cmd+S save.

1. Repo scaffold + `.claude/`, `.gitignore`, README, design assets
2. SwiftData models (`VirtualFolder`, `FileReference`, `AppState`, `ThemePreference`)
3. App shell — `NavigationSplitView` with sidebar + detail; theme wired via `.preferredColorScheme(...)`
4. `DesignTokens.swift` from the tokens JSON
5. Sidebar UI — folder list, search at top, download button bottom-left, three-dot hover menu, drag-reorder
6. File-add flows — file picker (`NSOpenPanel`) + Finder drag-drop
7. Editor view — editable `TextEditor` bound to the selected file's contents + SwiftUI top banner (file-name label, disabled view-mode segmented control stub, reserved trailing actions)
8. Save — Cmd+S writes UTF-8 to disk
9. Search — live filter on filenames + headings, ranked
10. Three-dot actions — Remove from app / Delete from disk
11. Settings scene — Light/Dark/Device theme picker (functional) + auto-save toggle (placeholder)
12. State restoration — folder structure, sidebar order, last-opened file, theme preference
13. Missing-file cleanup on launch (silent auto-remove)

### v1.1 — fixup iterations (post-MVP)

Each is a focused branch, mergeable independently:

- **Iteration A — Security-scoped bookmarks**: add `bookmarkData: Data` to `FileReference`, write a one-shot migration that re-resolves existing path-based refs into bookmarks on next launch. Inline "Locate..." UX replaces silent missing-file cleanup.
- **Iteration B — Three-mode rendering toggle (the hard part)**: replace `TextEditor` with `NSViewRepresentable`-wrapped `NSTextView`; implement Raw / Hybrid / Stylized via `NSTextStorage` attribute updates; toggle activates the segmented control in the editor toolbar. Default = Hybrid.
- **Iteration C — Auto-save + file watching**: wire `AppState.autoSaveEnabled`. ON = debounced write on edit. External-change watcher via `DispatchSourceFileSystemObject` always reloads.
- **Iteration D — Outline pane (right side)**: third column showing current document headings via the existing `HeadingParser`. Click-to-jump using `NSTextView` selection ranges.
- **Iteration E — Polish + hardening**: full Figma-token alignment pass, animations, light/dark refinement, app-icon integration when available, edge cases (empty folders, missing files, unmounted drives, very large files, unicode filenames, simultaneous external edits).

